data.title: 1435) – Find a Grave Gedenkstätte
data.meta_description: Also known as Leonor Urraca de Castilla, Eleanor was born in Aldeadávila de la Ribera to Sancho Alfonso, 1st Count of Alburquerque, and Beatrice of Portugal. She became the 3rd Countess of Alburquerque. She married Ferdinand (Fernando) I in 1394. They had seven children and became King and Queen of Aragon in 1412....
